  "prompt": "What social media etiquette do we often forget?",
  "response": "Here are some social media etiquette points people often forget:\n\n1. Personal boundaries\n- Not oversharing private details\n- Respecting others' privacy\n- Thinking before posting\n\n2. Engagement\n- Listening and understanding before commenting\n- Avoiding unnecessary arguments\n- Being constructive in discussions\n\n3. Consent and content\n- Asking permission before tagging\n- Not sharing others' personal photos without consent\n- Giving credit for shared content\n\n4. Tone and communication\n- Being respectful\n- Avoiding aggressive or inflammatory language\n- Using appropriate language\n\n5. Digital footprint\n- Remembering posts are permanent\n- Understanding potential professional consequences\n- Considering how content might be perceived\n\n6. Platform-specific norms\n- Understanding different platform cultures\n- Adapting communication style\n- Knowing appropriate content for each platform\n\n7. Fact-checking\n- Verifying information before sharing\n- Not spreading misinformation\n- Being critical of sources\n\n8. Time and frequency\n- Not overwhelming followers\n- Balancing personal and professional content\n- Being mindful of posting times\n\n9. Empathy and emotional intelligence\n- Considering others' feelings\n- Practicing digital kindness\n- Avoiding trolling or bullying\n\n10. Personal brand management\n- Presenting an authentic self\n- Maintaining consistent, positive representation",
